line_1: I Love thee more then Life or Interest,
line_2: Nor hast thou any Rival in my Breast;

line_1: And had by Turns chief Interest,
line_2: For both were of my Heart possess'd,
Such heated crimes as yet did never rest

line_1: I find, no selfish Grief, or Interest
line_2: Cou'd draw those Generous Murmurs from thy Breast.
